The issue appears to be in the `select()` method when handling the group/comma operator. When `tq.matchChomp(",")` is true, the code enters a `while (!tq.isEmpty())` loop that consumes all remaining tokens with `tq.chompTo(",")` and processes them. However, after this inner while loop completes, the outer while loop continues, but `tq` is now empty. This can cause issues if the loop condition or subsequent operations expect certain state.

More critically, the inner while loop uses `tq.chompTo(",")` which will consume everything up to the next comma. But after processing all comma-separated subqueries, when the inner loop exits (because `tq.isEmpty()`), the outer loop will try to continue but `tq` is empty. The logic seems correct for that case since the outer loop will also exit.

